Direct Line Insurance Group Plc

Direct Line Insurance is listed on the London Stock Exchange under the ticker DLG. Direct Line is a multi-line insurance company based in the United Kingdom. It is the UK's largest motor insurer. The company's brands include Direct Line, Churchill, and Privilege. The company was founded in 1985.

Direct Line has a market capitalisation of Â£2.65 billion, with approximately 1.31 billion shares in issue. Direct Line plc has over 5 million customers and employs over 7,000 people. The company primarily focuses on personal insurance products, including car, home, pet, life, travel, and rescue insurance. However, it also caters products to small- & medium-sized businesses.

